comments.body:
[~gholms] Can you see the [pull request|https://github.com/eucalyptus/eucalyptus/pull/16] and let me know what you think?  Specifically can you look at the content which is produced and whether it is sufficient.

The above change will generate a WSDL on a per-service basis (so, also public services which are serving other APIs at the moment).  The WSDL is annotated with the Query protocol field information and accounts for cases where the SOAP and Query protocols deviate.

To use (assumes CLC can be built):
{code}
( cd eucalyptus/clc
  ant jar # or a 'make' is fine, too.
  ../devel/groovy.sh ./modules/msgs/src/main/java/generate-xsd.groovy
)
{code}

At the moment I am principally concerned with getting the content in shape, clear and accurate, and so I expect to be polishing the usage (and build-time production of the documents) beyond this.
